---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Hip Pain"
	heroSubtitle="Hip pain can affect how you walk, sit, train and move day to day. It often builds gradually, but can also come on suddenly."
	breadcrumb="Hip Pain"
	seoTitle="Hip Pain Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert hip pain treatment in Clapham. We look at joint irritation, tendon overload and movement issues to help you reduce pain and move with confidence again."
	introImage="/condition/hip-pain/karate-kick.jpg"
	whoImage="/condition/hip-pain/gymnast-pose.jpg"
	intro={[
		"Hip pain can affect how you walk, sit, train and move day to day. It often builds gradually, but it can also come on suddenly — sometimes for no reason or after a change in activity or injury.",
		"We examine the underlying cause — whether joint irritation, pathology, tendon overload or movement issues — to help you reduce pain and move with confidence again.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get your hip"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsList={[
		"Pain in the front of the hip or groin during walking or exercise",
		"Pain in the knee, especially at night",
		"Discomfort on the outside of the hip when lying on that side",
		"Stiffness when getting up from sitting or after rest",
		"Pain when squatting, lunging or going up stairs",
		"A catching, clicking or unstable feeling in the hip",
		"Symptoms that spread into the groin, thigh or lower gluteal areas",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="hip pain"
	treatmentIntro="Your treatment plan is built around your specific presentation and may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve movement patterns and control",
		"Targeted strengthening to support the hip and surrounding muscles",
		"Manual therapy to reduce stiffness and ease discomfort",
		"Load management and education to help you stay active without aggravating symptoms",
		"Hydrotherapy to strengthen both limbs without aggravating any underlying pathology",
		"Movement retraining to improve how you walk, run and train",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Desk-based professionals dealing with stiffness from prolonged sitting",
		"Runners and athletes managing hip pain linked to training load",
		"Gym users working through strength or mobility limitations",
		"Seniors looking to stay mobile and confident in movement",
		"Active individuals who want to move without pain day to day",
		"People with recurring hip issues who want a clear and structured plan",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What is the most common cause of hip pain?", a: "In those under 40, hip pain often comes from tendon overload or muscle imbalance which reduces strength and control around the hip. For our seniors it can be for similar reasons or issues of aging or pathology (arthritis)." },
		{ q: "Should I stop exercising with hip pain?", a: "Not normally. We help you modify your activity so you can stay active while your hip recovers. Your hip will benefit greatly from increased strength and control." },
		{ q: "Can hip pain come from my back?", a: "Yes. The hip and lower back are closely linked, and symptoms can overlap. We assess both areas." },
		{ q: "Do I need a scan?", a: "In most cases, no. We can assess your hip thoroughly in the clinic and refer if needed." },
		{ q: "Can osteopathy help with hip pain?", a: "Yes, particularly for joint stiffness and movement restrictions." },
		{ q: "Will I get exercises to do at home?", a: "Yes. You'll be given specific exercises to support your recovery and rehabilitate your hip." },
	]}
/>
